run with java -jar assignment6.jar {args}

args:
	--rand {length} {filepath}
	--read {filepath 1} {filepath 2}

rand flag:
	creates an array with random entries of length {length} and saves it to {filepath}
read flag:
	reads the array at {filepath 1} and writes it to {filepath 2}

example usage:
	java -jar assignment6.jar --rand 50 ./filename
		creates a random array of length and saves it to the file filename
	java -jar assignment6.jar --read ./array1 ./sortedArray
		reads the array saved in the file array1, sorts it, and saves it to the file sortedArray